                     <hi rend="largeCaps">HENRY HARDY</hi> (23)</persName>
                  <rs id="t18640711-694-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18640711-694-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18640711-694-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>, Stealing 1 handkerchief, the property of <persName id="t18640711-name-211" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-211" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-211" type="surname" value="HOOPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-211" type="given" value="JOHN WILLETTS"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18640711-694-offence-1 t18640711-name-211"></join>John Willetts Hooper</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. COOPER</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution, and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. COLLINS</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">the Defence.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18640711-name-212" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-212" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-212" type="surname" value="HOOPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-212" type="given" value="JOHN WILLETTS"></interp>JOHN WILLETTS HOOPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at 21, Cloudesley-square, Islington—I am in no business—on 13th June I was in Farringdon-street, felt a tug at my pocket, and missed my handkerchief—I turned round immediately, and collared the prisoner, who was closer to me than anybody else—I held him some few minutes till I got a policeman—he offered me his handkerchief or anything about him if I would let him go—this is my handkerchief (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>).</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Were there any other people about? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I did not notice, but the prisoner was close to me—I did not see my handkerchief in his hand, but he pulled out an old one and offered me if I would let him go.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18640711-name-213" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-213" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-213" type="surname" value="BREWER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-213" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD BREWER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a smith, and live at 17, West Smithfield—I saw the prisoner take the prosecutor's handkerchief out of his pocket, but did not see what he did with it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> How far were you from him? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Four or five yards—I was crossing the road to get to the side were he was—there were five or six people round, close to the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18640711-name-214" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-214" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-214" type="surname" value="LAMMAS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18640711-name-214" type="given" value="JAMES ALFRED"></interp>JAMES ALFRED LAMMAS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City-policeman,</hi> 274). I was on duty on Holborn<lb></lb>bridge just before 10 o'clock, and took the prisoner in custody—I saw his arm go over the railing of some ruins—I looked over, and saw a handkerchief—I got a boy to get over and pick it up for me—this is it—I took the prisoner to the station, searched him, and found on him a handker<lb></lb>chief, which he said was his own, which he had had five years, a tobacco-box, and sevenpence.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> How far were you from him when you saw him lift his arm? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> About a dozen yards—there were other people round him, I am sure it was the prisoner.</p>
